The Senate Committee on Public Safety offered the following
substitute to SB 75:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 14 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to use
2 of speed detection devices and red light cameras, so as to provide for standards for signs
3 warning of the use of automated traffic enforcement safety devices; to require the use of a
4 sign or device which depicts an accurate representation of a vehicle's speed upon the
5 approach of an automated traffic enforcement safety device; to revise exceptions for when
6 a case may be made with the use of a speed detection device; to provide for times when a
7 school zone speed limit may be enforced through the use of an automated traffic enforcement
8 safety device; to provide for definitions; to amend Title 15 of the Official Code of Georgia
9 Annotated, relating to courts, so as to authorize district attorneys, solicitors-general, and
10 prosecuting attorneys to enforce civil monetary penalties relative to the enforcement of laws
11 regarding speeding in a school zone using recorded images; to provide for related matters;
12 to provide for effective dates and applicability; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
13 purposes.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
