15 SECTION 1.
16 Chapter 14 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to use of speed
17 detection devices and red light cameras, is amended in Code Section 40-14-1.1, relating to
18 definitions, by revising paragraph (5) and adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
19 "(5) 'School zone' means the area within 1,000 feet of the boundary of defined in an
20 existing master state order of the Department of Transportation and the Department of
21 Public Safety or local ordinance as a school zone area for any public or private
22 elementary or secondary school.
23 (6) 'School zone speed limit' means the speed limit set for a school zone in the approved
24 list of roads and master state order of the Department of Transportation and the
25 Department of Public Safety; provided, however, that such speed limit shall not vary for
26 a period that exceeds one hour more than twice a day."
27 SECTION 2.
28 Said chapter is further amended in Code Section 40-14-6, relating to warning signs required
29 and signage requirements, by revising subsection (c) as follows:
30 "(c) In addition to the signs required under subsections (a) and (b) of this Code section,
31 each law enforcement agency using an automated traffic enforcement safety device as
32 provided for in Code Section 40-14-18 shall erect signs which display the school zone
33 speed limit and signs warning of the use of a stationary speed detection an automated
34 traffic enforcement safety device within the approaching such school zone. Such signs
35 shall be at least 24 by 30 inches in area, shall be visible plainly from every lane of traffic,
36 shall be viewable in all traffic conditions, and shall not be placed in such a manner that the
37 view of such sign is subject to being obstructed by any other vehicle on such highway.
38 Such signs shall be placed within 500 feet prior to the warning sign announcing the
39 reduction of the speed limit for the school speed zone. Such signs which display the school
40 zone speed limit and warning of the use of an automated traffic enforcement safety device
