41 shall be placed upon every highway which leads to a school zone at a location one-half
42 mile from the start of the school zone and at any junction which intersects upon a highway
43 leading to a school between the school and such one-half mile location; provided, however,
44 that, when such one-half mile location is outside of the jurisdictional boundaries of a law
45 enforcement agency or such highway has a length of less than one-half mile from the
46 school zone, such signs shall be placed at the jurisdictional boundary of the law
47 enforcement agency or at a location as close to such one-half mile location as practicable.
48 A sign or device which provides an accurate depiction of the speed of an approaching
49 motor vehicle shall be placed upon a sign warning of the use of an automated traffic
50 enforcement safety device or as a stand-alone sign between such warning signs and the
51 outermost boundary of a school zone. Additional signs which display the school zone
52 speed limit and which include lights which flash yellow in accordance with rules and
53 regulations of the Department of Transportation while the school zone speed limit is in
54 effect and when the automated traffic enforcement safety device is authorized to issue
55 citations pursuant to Code Section 40-14-18 shall be placed at the outermost boundary of
56 a school zone. There shall be a rebuttable presumption that such signs are properly
57 installed pursuant to this subsection at the time of any alleged violation under this article."
58 SECTION 3.
59 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 40-14-8, relating to when case may
60 be made and conviction had, as follows:
61 "40-14-8.
62 (a) No county, city, or campus officer shall be allowed to make a case based on the use of
63 any speed detection device, unless the speed of the vehicle exceeds the posted speed limit
64 by more than ten miles per hour and no conviction shall be had thereon unless such speed
65 is more than ten miles per hour above the posted speed limit.
